  "title": "Heidelberg Q48",
  "body": "But if his human nature is not present, wherever his Godhead is, are not then these two natures in Christ separated from one another?\n\nNot at all; for since the Godhead is illimitable and omnipresent, it must necessarily follow that the same is not limited with the human nature he assumed, and yet remains personally united to it.",
